 solid; background-color: #ccc;">funny IRON postmortem</a> that points out =
that, for a while, you=C2=A0<em>couldn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>get your $0.74 b=
ack:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">After the collapse of TITA=
N, there were still $0.74 worth of USDC in the IRON treasury for every 1 IR=
ON outstanding. It can be redeemed by the IRON contract itself at any momen=
t regardless of the price in the market (currently ~$0.71). The remainder t=
owards a full $1 was to be payed out in TITAN, but obviously that part is i=
rrelevant now.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In practice it looks a littl=
e different. I=E2=80=99ve mentioned in the beginning the the whole episode =
isn=E2=80=99t over yet, because $272 million worth of USDC is still locked =
up in in the contract. Why hasn=E2=80=99t everyone recovered their 74 cents=
? <strong>Here things become <em>truly hilarious</em>.</strong> It is due t=
