ed close to stores that sell jackpot-winning tickets buy more stock shares =
than their counterparts. More importantly, these retail buys tend to lose m=
oney. We also find that these retail investors tend to purchase lottery-lik=
e stocks, linking the luck-driven trading motive to the traded targets unde=
r the common theme of gambling. We substantiate our results via several set=
s of falsification tests and robustness checks. Overall, feeling lucky indu=
ces retail investors to trade aggressively and leads to welfare losses.</p>=
